Optional fcitx-mozkey / Mozc sidecar
------------------------------------

Project: https://github.com/Masterisk-F/fcitx-mozkey

Experimental builds made with `HAZKEY_SERVER_MOZC_ARTIFACT_DIR` additionally
include a converter helper built from Masterisk-F/fcitx-mozkey revision
462cbbf04886e32096bc318833e974ccc43d9fc8 and the fixed Mozc OSS dataset. Those
builds install the complete fixed-input license set under
`mozc-sidecar/` beside this file. Artifact import fails if any required notice
is absent or has a different checksum.

The fixed source contains Mozc-derived BSD 3-Clause code, separately licensed
dictionary data, and statically linked components. The installed notice set
includes the fixed upstream license and third-party notice, the OSS dictionary
terms, and the licenses of the linked Abseil, Protocol Buffers, UTF8 Range, and
Japanese usage dictionary inputs.
